---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/ui/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/ui/Footer.astro';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    {
      params: { slug: 'global-labor-trends-2024' },
      props: {
        post: {
          slug: 'global-labor-trends-2024',
          title: 'Global Labor Market Trends in 2024',
          content: `
            <p class="lead">The global labor market is undergoing significant transformations in 2024, driven by technological advancements, changing economic landscapes, and evolving workforce expectations. Understanding these trends is crucial for both job seekers and employers in the international labor market.</p>
            
            <h2>Key Trends Shaping 2024</h2>
            
            <h3>1. Digital Skills Dominance</h3>
            <p>Digital literacy is no longer optional but essential. From basic computer skills to advanced programming, digital competencies are becoming mandatory across all industries and job roles. Workers who embrace continuous learning in technology will have a significant advantage.</p>
            
            <h3>2. Remote Work Integration</h3>
            <p>Hybrid work models are becoming standard practice, creating new opportunities for cross-border employment without physical relocation. This trend is particularly beneficial for professionals in developing countries seeking international opportunities.</p>
            
            <h3>3. Green Economy Jobs</h3>
            <p>The global transition to sustainable practices is creating entirely new job categories in renewable energy, environmental conservation, and sustainable manufacturing. These roles often come with competitive international packages.</p>
            
            <h2>Regional Opportunities Analysis</h2>
            
            <p>Different regions are experiencing varying demands for skilled labor in 2024:</p>
            
            <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-6">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-3">High-Demand Regions</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary-600 mr-2">•</span>
                  <span><strong>Middle East:</strong> Construction supervisors, healthcare professionals, IT specialists, and engineering roles</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary-600 mr-2">•</span>
                  <span><strong>Europe:</strong> Healthcare workers, software engineers, skilled tradespeople, and renewable energy technicians</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary-600 mr-2">•</span>
                  <span><strong>North America:</strong> Technology professionals, healthcare staff, and professional services roles</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="text-primary-600 mr-2">•</span>
                  <span><strong>Asia-Pacific:</strong> Manufacturing supervisors, hospitality management, and technical training roles</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>Salary and Benefits Trends</h2>
            
            <p>International compensation packages are becoming more competitive, with employers offering:</p>
            
            <ul>
              <li>Higher base salaries compared to local markets</li>
              <li>Comprehensive health insurance coverage</li>
              <li>Housing allowances and relocation support</li>
              <li>Professional development opportunities</li>
              <li>Family relocation packages</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Future Outlook</h2>
            
            <p>The demand for skilled international labor is expected to grow by 15-20% annually through 2026. Professionals with specialized technical skills, language abilities, and cultural adaptability will be in particularly high demand.</p>
            
            <div class="bg-secondary-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-6 border-l-4 border-secondary-500">
              <p class="text-secondary-800 font-semibold">Pro Tip: Start preparing now by upgrading your digital skills and learning about the cultural norms of your target destination countries.</p>
            </div>
          `,
          date: 'March 15, 2024',
          author: 'Sarah Johnson',
          category: 'Market Insights',
          readTime: '5 min read'
        }
      }
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'visa-process-simplified' },
      props: {
        post: {
          slug: 'visa-process-simplified',
          title: 'Visa Processing Simplified: A Complete Guide',
          content: 'Complete guide content...',
          date: 'March 10, 2024',
          author: 'Mike Chen',
          category: 'Visa Guide',
          readTime: '7 min read'
        }
      }
    },
    // Add other posts...
  ];
}

const { post } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout 
  title={post.title}
  description={post.excerpt || post.content.substring(0, 160)}
  canonical={`https://globalwork-labor.com/blog/${post.slug}`}
>
  <Header />
  
  <!-- Blog Post Header -->
  <section class="bg-white py-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a 
          href="/blog"
          class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 mb-6 transition-colors font-semibold"
        >
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"/>
          </svg>
          Back to Blog
        </a>
        
        <div class="mb-8">
          <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">
            {post.category}
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
          {post.title}
        </h1>
        
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-2 md:space-y-0">
          <div class="flex items-center mr-6">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
            </svg>
            <span>{post.date}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center mr-6">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"/>
            </svg>
            <span>{post.author}</span>
          </div>
          {post.readTime && (
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
              </svg>
              <span>{post.readTime}</span>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blog Content -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <article class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 md:p-12">
          <div 
            class="prose prose-lg max-w-none"
            set:html={post.content}
          ></div>
          
          <!-- Share Section -->
          <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Share this article</h4>
            <div class="flex space-x-4">
              <a href="#" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M24 12.073c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12s-12 5.373-12 12c0 5.99 4.388 10.954 10.125 11.854v-8.385H7.078v-3.47h3.047V9.43c0-3.007 1.792-4.669 4.533-4.669 1.312 0 2.686.235 2.686.235v2.953H15.83c-1.491 0-1.956.925-1.956 1.874v2.25h3.328l-.532 3.47h-2.796v8.385C19.612 23.027 24 18.062 24 12.073z"/>
                </svg>
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M23.953 4.57a10 10 0 01-2.825.775 4.958 4.958 0 002.163-2.723 10.016 10.016 0 01-3.127 1.195 4.92 4.92 0 00-8.384 4.482C7.69 8.095 4.067 6.13 1.64 3.162a4.822 4.822 0 00-.666 2.475c0 1.71.87 3.213 2.188 4.096a4.904 4.904 0 01-2.228-.616v.06a4.923 4.923 0 003.946 4.827 4.996 4.996 0 01-2.212.085 4.937 4.937 0 004.604 3.417 9.868 9.868 0 01-6.102 2.105c-.39 0-.779-.023-1.17-.067a13.995 13.995 0 007.557 2.209c9.054 0 13.999-7.496 13.999-13.986 0-.209 0-.42-.015-.63a9.936 9.936 0 002.46-2.543l-.047-.02z"/>
                </svg>
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M20.447 20.452h-3.554v-5.569c0-1.328-.027-3.037-1.852-3.037-1.853 0-2.136 1.445-2.136 2.939v5.667H9.351V9h3.414v1.561h.046c.477-.9 1.637-1.85 3.37-1.85 3.601 0 4.267 2.37 4.267 5.455v6.286zM5.337 7.433c-1.144 0-2.063-.926-2.063-2.065 0-1.138.92-2.063 2.063-2.063 1.14 0 2.064.925 2.064 2.063 0 1.139-.925 2.065-2.064 2.065zm1.782 13.019H3.555V9h3.564v11.452zM22.225 0H1.771C.792 0 0 .774 0 1.729v20.542C0 23.227.792 24 1.771 24h20.451C23.2 24 24 23.227 24 22.271V1.729C24 .774 23.2 0 22.222 0h.003z"/>
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Related Posts -->
        <div class="mt-16">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Related Articles</h3>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <!-- You can add related posts here -->
            <a href="/blog/skills-in-demand" class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow border border-gray-200">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Top 10 Skills in Demand for International Jobs</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Learn which skills are most sought after by employers worldwide in 2024.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/cultural-adaptation" class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow border border-gray-200">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cultural Adaptation: Thriving Abroad</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Essential tips for adapting to new cultures and work environments.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .prose {
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    color: #111827;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.875em;
    margin-top: 2em;
    margin-bottom: 1em;
    line-height: 1.3333333;
  }
  
  .prose h3 {
    color: #111827;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.5em;
    margin-top: 1.6em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6em;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-top: 1.25em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25em;
  }
  
  .prose ul {
    margin-top: 1.25em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25em;
    padding-left: 1.625em;
  }
  
  .prose li {
    margin-top: 0.5em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5em;
  }
  
  .prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.25em;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #4b5563;
  }
</style>